definition:
A man of the tribe of Judah living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at 2Ch.21.2; 
 son of: Jehoshaphat (H3092I); 
 brother of: Jehoram (H3088), Azariah (H5838Q), Jehiel (H3171J), Azariahu (H5838R), Michael (H4317O) and Shephatiah (H8203K)
 § Zechariah = "Jehovah remembers"
 11th in order of the minor prophets; a priest, son of Berechiah and grandson of Iddo, who, along with Haggai, directed the rebuilding of the temple in the days of Zerubbabel
